        "source_url": "https://thaqalayn.net/hadith/34/3/86/1",
        "text": [
          " : قُلْتُ لِأَبِي عَبْدِ اَللَّهِ عَلَيْهِ اَلسَّلاَمُ حَجَّةُ اَلْجَمَّالِ تَامَّةٌ أَمْ نَاقِصَةٌ قَالَ «تَامَّةٌ» قُلْتُ حَجَّةُ اَلْأَجِيرِ تَامَّةٌ أَوْ نَاقِصَةٌ قَالَ «تَامَّةٌ."
        ],
        "translations": {
          "en.bab-ul-qaim-publications": [
            "Hadith.2881 - It was narrated from Mu'awiyah ibn Ammar, who said:\nI said to Abu Abdullah (as): \"Is the Hajj of a camel driver complete or incomplete?\"\nImam (as) said: \"It is complete.\"\nI asked: \"Is the Hajj of a hired worker complete or incomplete?\"\nImam (as) said: \"It is complete.\""
          ]
        }
      }
